                          Personal income tax: rate.</span></div><div><span id="digesttext"><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">The Personal Income Tax Law, in modified conformity with federal income tax law, imposes taxes on taxable income, as provided.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">This bill, for taxable years beginning on or after January 1, 2025, and before January 1, 2030, would revise the income tax rates and taxable income brackets by imposing an income tax rate of 1%, 3%, 5%, or 7%, instead of 2%, 4%, 6%, or 8%, as applicable, on specified taxable income.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">This bill would take effect immediately as a tax levy.</div></i></font><font color="#B30000"><strike><p style="display:inline;"><s>The Personal Income Tax Law, in modified conformity with federal income tax law, imposes taxes on taxable income, as provided.</s></p><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"></div><p style="display:inline;"><s>This bill, for taxable years beginning on or after January 1, 2025, would revise the income tax rates and taxable income brackets by imposing an income tax rate of 3% instead of 4%, increasing as applicable, on specified taxable income.</s></p><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"></div><p style="display:inline;"><s>This bill would take effect immediately as a tax levy.</s></p><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"></div></strike></font></span></div><span class="hidden"><h2>Digest Key</h2></span><span id="vote">
      Vote:
      <span style=" text-transform: lowercase">MAJORITY</span>  </span><span id="appropriation">
