      <span style=" text-transform: lowercase">NO</span>  </span><span id="fiscalcommittee">
      Fiscal Committee:
      <span style=" text-transform: lowercase">YES</span>  </span><span id="localprogram">
      Local Program:
      <span style=" text-transform: lowercase">NO</span>  </span></div><hr/><span class="hidden"><h2>Bill Text</h2></span><div id="bill"><div style=" text-transform: uppercase"><h2 style=" text-align: left;">The people of the State of California do enact as follows:</h2><br/></div><div id="s10.7651041012954297"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0" class="ActionLine"><h3 style="font-weight:bold; display:inline;"><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i>SECTION 1.</i></font></h3> <font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i>Section 17041 of the Revenue and Taxation Code is amended to read:</i></font></div><div><div id="id_347DD7C2-448C-4183-A41F-47D74A57DC68"><div><p><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"><h6 style="display:inline;">17041.</h6> (a) (1) There shall be imposed for each taxable year upon the entire taxable income of every resident of this state who is not a part-year resident, except the head of a<font color="#B30000"><strike> household</strike></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i> household,</i></font> as defined in Section 17042, taxes in the following amounts and at the following rates upon the amount of taxable income computed for the taxable year as if the resident were a resident of this state for the entire taxable year and for all prior taxable years for any carryover items, deferred income, suspended losses, or suspended deductions:</div><table frame=""><tr><td><div style="font-size:10pt; text-align:left; ; text-indent:0pt;">If the taxable income is:</div></td><td><div style="font-size:10pt; text-align:left; hyphenation: yes;; text-indent:0pt;">The tax is:</div></td></tr><tr><td><div style="font-size:10pt; text-align:left; ; text-indent:0pt;">Not over $3,650 
