						part-year resident were a resident of this state for all prior taxable years for any carryover items, deferred income, suspended losses, or suspended deductions, divided by the amount of that income.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">(c) (1) There shall be imposed for each taxable year upon the entire taxable income of every resident of this state who is not a part-year resident for that taxable year, when the resident is the head of a household, as defined in Section 17042, taxes in the following amounts and at the following rates upon the amount of taxable income computed for the taxable year as if the resident were a resident of the state for the entire taxable year and for all prior taxable years for carryover items, deferred income, suspended losses, or suspended deductions:</div><table frame=""><tr><td><div style="font-size:10pt; text-align:left; ; text-indent:0pt;">If the taxable income is:</div></td><td><div style="font-size:10pt; text-align:left; hyphenation: yes;; text-indent:0pt;">The tax is:</div></td></tr><tr><td><div style="font-size:10pt; text-align:left; ; text-indent:0pt;">Not over $7,300 
